 “a way out” from a studio with successful previous project and “anthem” from an experienced studio bioware finally ea presented “battlefront ” a sequel to a commercially successful game this time it offers a lot of new features for example a more complete storymode and wider multiplayer experience recommendation in my opinion electronic arts despite its ups and downs with revenue growth is one of the most efficient companies on the market ea has been improving its cost margins for several years dcf valuation shows that company has potential to grow analysis of multiples for competitors also shows that company may be undervalued from qualitative side company also shows that it knows that it needs to work with both existing properties and new projects from proven teams disclosure iwe have no positions in any stocks mentioned and no plans to initiate any positions within the next  hours i wrote this article myself and it expresses my own opinions i am not receiving compensation for it other than from seeking alpha i have no business relationship with any company whose stock is mentioned in this articleabout this articleexpandauthor payment   page view authors of pro articles receive a minimum guaranteed payment of tagged investing ideas long ideas technology multimedia  graphics softwarewant to share your opinion on this article add a commentdisagree with this article submit your ownto report a factual error in this article click herefollow alexander kalashnikov and get email alerts electronic arts home page  official ea site the sims console edition coming discover the game dont miss ea at gamescom  gamescom more news more gameplay and more handson experiences for our players tune in on august  for the live show build unique cars need for speed payback whether its buying cars picking up new parts or finding a sweet new now youll have even more ways to interact with and customize your favorite rides join inferno squad star wars battlefront ii in a galaxy of conflict n