  ea north carolina in morrisville north carolina closed in  victory games in los angeles california also has offices in austin texas and shanghai china founded in  and closed down in  as danger close mythic entertainment in fairfax virginia founded as interworld productions in  acquired in june  and closed down in may  maxis in emeryville california founded in  acquired in july  and closed down in march  waystone was disbanded in november  ea partners programedit the ea partners copublishing arm is dedicated to publishing and distributing games developed by thirdparty developers notable publishingdistribution agreements include alice madness returns – spicy horse apb – realtime worlds brütal legend – double fine productions bulletstorm – epic games crysis series – crytek deathspank – hothead games fuse – insomniac games hellgate london – flagship studios kingdoms of amalur reckoning –  studios big huge games rock band series – harmonix and mtv games the secret world – funcom shadows of the damned – grasshopper manufacture shank series – klei entertainment syndicate – starbreeze studios titanfall series – respawn entertainment warp – trapdoor ea originals programedit ea originals is a program within electronic arts to help support independentlydeveloped video games the program was announced at eas press event at the  e conference and builds upon the success they had with unravel in  the first game to be supported under this program is fe by zoink games with plans for release in  it will be followed by sea of solitude and a way out games by electronic artsedit main article list of electronic arts games some of the most notable and popular games of video game history have been published by ea and many of these are listed below though ea published these titles they did not always develop them some were developed by independent game development studios ea developed their first internally developed game in  pinball construction set  by bill budge mule  by dan bunten and 